The while loop is infinite in part because the request for input is commented out and sscanf has nothing to parse.  
Another issue may be the use of `%s` to parse `itemName`. If there are spaces in `itemName`, %s will stop at the first space. If you want to use a comma to delimit the values, `%s` will treat the comma as just another character as part of `itemName`.  
A scanset can help with that. The scanset `%[^,]` tells sscanf to scan characters that are not a comma and put them in `itemName`. So `%49[^,],` will scan up to 49 characters that are not a comma and then scan the comma.  
Consider using `fgets` for all input and parse with sscanf. Some other useful functions for parsing are `strtol`, `strtod`, `strspn` and `strcspn`. There are many more.  

