You need a series of steps (assuming there is no already assigned unique key). 

 1. Add a temporary column to make each row unique.
 2. Assign a value to the new columns.
 3. Remove the already existing duplicates.
 4. Create a Unique or Primary Key on the composite columns.
 5. Remove the temporary column.

&lt;!-- --&gt;

    alter table your_table add temp_unique integer unique;
          
    do $$
    declare
        row_num  integer = 1;
        c_assign cursor for
            select temp_unique 
              from your_table
               for update;
    begin 
        for rec in c_assign
        loop
           update your_table 
              set temp_unique = row_num
            where current of c_assign;
           row_num = row_num + 1;
        end loop; 
    end; 
    $$
    
